      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Interesting entry here with import SEE THAT STORM (8) who makes his local debut for the Price & Kent yard. He is off nearly a year spell but was given a strong hitout in his latest trial win over 1400m. His last start effort at York when second was good - the winner has gone right on with it since to frank the form. He looks very well placed with 54kg against a few that don't do a whole lot of winning. EL ROCKO (2) has been well backed early on the quick backup having gone for home early last week at Sandown, fading late over 1400m. If he gets control he'll give a huge sight on his favoured wet ground. OH TOO GOOD (3) finished just ahead of VERDAD last time and is in the each way mix again while JIMMY THE BEAR (1) should improve sharply to a mile but pays for his record at the weights.",
